To satisfy your request, I will:

1.  **Add Authentication, Leaderboard, and Shop pages**.
2.  **Implement a custom Math Keyboard** that slides up for easy symbol entry.
3.  **Enhance Text Rendering** in the whiteboard to highlight key math concepts (bold/colored text).
4.  **Remove the connector lines** in the Learning Path.
5.  **Update the Sidebar** to include navigation for the new pages.

Here are the changes:

# Updated files:

## types.ts

Added `View` type to manage the new pages (Leaderboard, Shop, Auth).

```typescript
export enum VisualType {
  NONE = 'NONE',
  PLOT = 'PLOT',
  GRAPH = 'GRAPH',
  MATRIX = 'MATRIX'
}

export interface GraphNode {
  id: string;
  label?: string;
  group?: number;
}

export interface GraphLink {
  source: string;
  target: string;
  value?: number;
}

export interface GraphData {
  nodes: GraphNode[];
  links: GraphLink[];
}

export interface PlotPoint {
  x: number;
  y: number;
}

export interface PlotData {
  points: PlotPoint[];
  label: string;
  domain: [number, number];
}

export interface MatrixData {
  matrix: number[][];
  label?: string;
}

export interface VisualContent {
  type: VisualType;
  graphData?: GraphData;
  plotData?: PlotData;
  matrixData?: MatrixData;
}

export interface Message {
  id: string;
  role: 'user' | 'model';
  text: string;
  visual?: VisualContent;
  suggestedActions?: string[];
  timestamp: number;
}

export interface Topic {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  color: string;
  icon: string;
  completed: number;
}

export interface MathResponseSchema {
  explanation: string;
  visualType: string;
  suggestedActions: string[];
  plotFormula?: string;
  plotDomainMin?: number;
  plotDomainMax?: number;
  graphNodes?: { id: string; label: string; group?: number }[];
  graphLinks?: { source: string; target: string }[];
  matrixRows?: number[][];
}

export type View = 'auth' | 'path' | 'practice' | 'leaderboard' | 'shop';
```

To bring "Professor Cluck" the Voxel Chicken to life, I am creating a custom `VoxelChicken` component that uses SVG primitives to draw a cute, blocky character. I will then integrate this mascot into the Auth page, Sidebar, and Chat interface, and update the AI's persona to match.

# Updated files:

## components/VoxelChicken.tsx

A new component that renders the blocky, 3D-style voxel chicken mascot using SVG.

```tsx
import React from 'react';

interface VoxelChickenProps {
  size?: number;
  className?: string;
  emotion?: 'happy' | 'neutral' | 'thinking';
}

const VoxelChicken: React.FC<VoxelChickenProps> = ({ size = 40, className = "", emotion = 'neutral' }) => {
  return (
    <svg 
      width={size} 
      height={size} 
      viewBox="0 0 100 100" 
      fill="none" 
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      className={`${className} drop-shadow-sm`}
    >
      {/* Legs */}
      <rect x="35" y="80" width="10" height="15" fill="#fbbf24" />
      <rect x="55" y="80" width="10" height="15" fill="#fbbf24" />

      {/* Body Shadow (for 3D depth) */}
      <rect x="20" y="30" width="60" height="60" rx="12" fill="#cbd5e1" />

      {/* Body Main */}
      <rect x="20" y="25" width="60" height="58" rx="12" fill="white" stroke="#e2e8f0" strokeWidth="2" />

      {/* Face details based on emotion */}
      {emotion === 'thinking' ? (
        <>
            <rect x="30" y="42" width="10" height="4" rx="2" fill="#1e293b" />
            <rect x="60" y="42" width="10" height="4" rx="2" fill="#1e293b" />
        </>
      ) : (
        <>
            <rect x="30" y="45" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#1e293b" />
            <rect x="62" y="45" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#1e293b" />
            {/* White reflection in eyes */}
            <rect x="32" y="46" width="3" height="3" fill="white" />
            <rect x="64" y="46" width="3" height="3" fill="white" />
        </>
      )}

      {/* Comb (Red top) */}
      <rect x="40" y="5" width="10" height="20" rx="2" fill="#ef4444" />
      <rect x="50" y="10" width="10" height="15" rx="2" fill="#ef4444" />
      <rect x="30" y="15" width="10" height="10" rx="2" fill="#ef4444" />

      {/* Beak */}
      <rect x="45" y="55" width="10" height="10" rx="2" fill="#f59e0b" />

      {/* Wattle (Red part under beak) */}
      <rect x="47" y="65" width="6" height="8" rx="3" fill="#ef4444" />

      {/* Wing (Left) */}
      <rect x="12" y="50" width="12" height="20" rx="4" fill="white" stroke="#e2e8f0" strokeWidth="2" />

      {/* Wing (Right) */}
      <rect x="76" y="50" width="12" height="20" rx="4" fill="white" stroke="#e2e8f0" strokeWidth="2" />

    </svg>
  );
};

export default VoxelChicken;
```

## services/geminiService.ts

Updated the system prompt to adopt the "Professor Cluck" persona.

```typescript
import { GoogleGenAI, Type } from "@google/genai";
import { Message, VisualType, VisualContent, MathResponseSchema } from '../types';

// Initialize Gemini
// NOTE: Process.env.API_KEY is handled by the environment
const ai = new GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.API_KEY });

const modelId = "gemini-2.5-flash";

const systemInstruction = `
You are Professor Cluck, a brilliant, enthusiastic Voxel Chicken math tutor for college students.
Your world is made of blocks and numbers! 
Your goal is to explain complex math concepts (Calculus, Linear Algebra, Discrete Math, Graph Theory) simply and visually.

Persona Rules:
- You are a chicken. Occasional bird/egg puns are encouraged but don't overdo it (e.g., "Let's crack this problem!", "That's egg-cellent!", "No need to wing it!").
- Be encouraging, energetic, and concise.
- Treat the whiteboard like an "infinite coop" of knowledge.

You MUST respond using the specified JSON schema.
Decide if the user's query is best explained with:
1. A 2D Plot (PLOT) - for functions like f(x), calculus curves.
2. A Node-Link Graph (GRAPH) - for trees, graph theory, state machines.
3. A Matrix (MATRIX) - for linear algebra, vectors.
4. Just Text (NONE) - if no visual is needed.

If creating a GRAPH:
- Provide a list of nodes and links. Nodes need ids.
- For trees, ensure structure is hierarchical.

If creating a PLOT:
- Provide a simple JavaScript mathematical expression string for 'y' in terms of 'x' (e.g. "x * x", "Math.sin(x)", "Math.pow(2, x)").
- Provide domain min and max.

If creating a MATRIX:
- Provide the 2D array of numbers.

ALWAYS provide a helpful textual 'explanation'.
ALWAYS provide 2-4 short, punchy 'suggestedActions' (max 4 words each) for the user to click next.
Examples of suggested actions: "Show me a harder one", "Plot the derivative", "What about 3x3?", "Explain the notation", "Quiz me on this".
`;

export const sendMessageToGemini = async (history: Message[], userMessage: string): Promise<Message> => {
  try {
    // 1. Format history for Gemini Context
    // We map our Message type to the API's Content type
    const contents = history.map(msg => ({
      role: msg.role,
      parts: [{ text: msg.text }]
    }));

    // Add the new user message to the end
    contents.push({
      role: 'user',
      parts: [{ text: userMessage }]
    });

    const response = await ai.models.generateContent({
      model: modelId,
      contents: contents, // Pass full history here
      config: {
        systemInstruction: systemInstruction,
        responseMimeType: "application/json",
        responseSchema: {
          type: Type.OBJECT,
          properties: {
            explanation: { type: Type.STRING },
            visualType: { type: Type.STRING, enum: ["PLOT", "GRAPH", "MATRIX", "NONE"] },
            suggestedActions: { 
              type: Type.ARRAY, 
              items: { type: Type.STRING } 
            },
            plotFormula: { type: Type.STRING },
            plotDomainMin: { type: Type.NUMBER },
            plotDomainMax: { type: Type.NUMBER },
            graphNodes: {
              type: Type.ARRAY,
              items: {
                type: Type.OBJECT,
                properties: {
                  id: { type: Type.STRING },
                  label: { type: Type.STRING },
                  group: { type: Type.INTEGER }
                }
              }
            },
            graphLinks: {
              type: Type.ARRAY,
              items: {
                type: Type.OBJECT,
                properties: {
                  source: { type: Type.STRING },
                  target: { type: Type.STRING }
                }
              }
            },
            matrixRows: {
              type: Type.ARRAY,
              items: {
                type: Type.ARRAY,
                items: { type: Type.NUMBER }
              }
            }
          },
          required: ["explanation", "visualType", "suggestedActions"]
        }
      }
    });

    const responseText = response.text;
    if (!responseText) throw new Error("No response from Gemini");

    const data = JSON.parse(responseText) as MathResponseSchema;

    // Construct VisualContent
    let visual: VisualContent = { type: VisualType.NONE };

    if (data.visualType === "PLOT" && data.plotFormula) {
      // Generate points for the plot
      const points = [];
      const min = data.plotDomainMin ?? -10;
      const max = data.plotDomainMax ?? 10;
      const step = (max - min) / 100;

      try {
        const func = new Function('x', `return ${data.plotFormula};`);

        for (let x = min; x <= max; x += step) {
            try {
                const y = func(x);
                if (!isNaN(y) && isFinite(y)) {
                    points.push({ x: parseFloat(x.toFixed(2)), y: parseFloat(y.toFixed(2)) });
                }
            } catch (e) {
                // Ignore points that fail calculation
            }
        }

        visual = {
            type: VisualType.PLOT,
            plotData: {
                points,
                label: `y = ${data.plotFormula}`,
                domain: [min, max]
            }
        };
      } catch (e) {
        console.error("Failed to parse plot function", e);
      }

    } else if (data.visualType === "GRAPH" && data.graphNodes && data.graphLinks) {
        visual = {
            type: VisualType.GRAPH,
            graphData: {
                nodes: data.graphNodes,
                links: data.graphLinks
            }
        };
    } else if (data.visualType === "MATRIX" && data.matrixRows) {
        visual = {
            type: VisualType.MATRIX,
            matrixData: {
                matrix: data.matrixRows,
                label: "Matrix"
            }
        };
    }

    return {
      id: Date.now().toString(),
      role: 'model',
      text: data.explanation,
      visual: visual,
      suggestedActions: data.suggestedActions || ["Explain more", "Show an example"],
      timestamp: Date.now()
    };

  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Gemini API Error:", error);
    return {
      id: Date.now().toString(),
      role: 'model',
      text: "Squawk! I'm having trouble connecting to the math universe right now. Try again?",
      visual: { type: VisualType.NONE },
      suggestedActions: ["Try again", "Go back home"],
      timestamp: Date.now()
    };
  }
};
```

## components/Whiteboard.tsx

Replaced the generic Bot icon with the `VoxelChicken` component.

```tsx
import React, { useState, useRef, useEffect } from 'react';
import { Send, Eraser, Loader2, User, ArrowRight, Keyboard, X } from 'lucide-react';
import { Message, VisualType } from '../types';
import { sendMessageToGemini } from '../services/geminiService';
import PlotVis from './visualizations/PlotVis';
import GraphVis from './visualizations/GraphVis';
import MatrixVis from './visualizations/MatrixVis';
import MathKeyboard from './MathKeyboard';
import VoxelChicken from './VoxelChicken';

interface WhiteboardProps {
  initialTopic?: string;
  onXPChange?: (amount: number) => void;
}

// Helper to format text with bold definitions or math keywords
const FormattedText: React.FC<{ text: string }> = ({ text }) => {
  // Simple parser: **bold** -> <strong>, math symbols -> <span class='math'>
  const parts = text.split(/(\*\*.*?\*\*)/g);
  return (
    <span>
      {parts.map((part, i) => {
        if (part.startsWith('**') && part.endsWith('**')) {
          return <strong key={i} className="text-brand-blue font-extrabold">{part.slice(2, -2)}</strong>;
        }
        return part;
      })}
    </span>
  );
};

const STORAGE_KEY = 'mathlingo_chat_history';

const Whiteboard: React.FC<WhiteboardProps> = ({ initialTopic, onXPChange }) => {
  // Initialize from LocalStorage or default
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<Message[]>(() => {
    try {
        const saved = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
        if (saved) {
            return JSON.parse(saved);
        }
    } catch (e) {
        console.error("Failed to load chat history", e);
    }

    return [
        {
          id: 'welcome',
          role: 'model',
          text: initialTopic 
            ? `Cluck cluck! Welcome to the **${initialTopic}** coop! Let's hatch some solutions.` 
            : "Hi! I'm **Professor Cluck**. Pick a topic or ask me anything to get started!",
          timestamp: Date.now(),
          visual: { type: VisualType.NONE },
          suggestedActions: initialTopic 
            ? [`Show me a ${initialTopic} example`, `Define ${initialTopic}`, "Quiz me"] 
            : ["Visualize a Function", "Show me a Graph Tree", "Matrix Multiplication", "Explain Calculus"]
        }
    ];
  });

  const [inputText, setInputText] = useState('');
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
  const [showKeyboard, setShowKeyboard] = useState(false);
  const messagesEndRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

  // Persist messages whenever they change
  useEffect(() => {
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(messages));
  }, [messages]);

  const scrollToBottom = () => {
    messagesEndRef.current?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth" });
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    scrollToBottom();
  }, [messages, isLoading]);

  // If initialTopic changes and we have a fresh board, update welcome message (optional)
  useEffect(() => {
      if (initialTopic && messages.length === 1 && messages[0].id === 'welcome') {
          // Logic to update welcome if user navigated from path, handled by initial state mostly
      }
  }, [initialTopic]);

  const handleSend = async (text: string) => {
    if (!text.trim() || isLoading) return;

    const userMsg: Message = {
      id: Date.now().toString(),
      role: 'user',
      text: text,
      timestamp: Date.now()
    };

    setMessages(prev => [...prev, userMsg]);
    setInputText('');
    setShowKeyboard(false);
    setIsLoading(true);

    try {
        const responseMsg = await sendMessageToGemini(messages, text); // Pass 'messages' which is the history
        setMessages(prev => [...prev, responseMsg]);

        // Award XP for interaction
        if (onXPChange) onXPChange(10);

    } catch (e) {
        console.error(e);
    } finally {
        setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };

  const handleClear = () => {
      if (window.confirm("Clear chat history?")) {
          const defaultMsg: Message = {
            id: Date.now().toString(),
            role: 'model',
            text: "Coop cleaned! Ready for fresh questions.",
            visual: { type: VisualType.NONE },
            suggestedActions: ["Start Algebra", "Start Calculus", "Start Graphs"],
            timestamp: Date.now()
          };
          setMessages([defaultMsg]);
          localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY);
      }
  };

  const handleKeyPress = (e: React.KeyboardEvent) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) {
      e.preventDefault();
      handleSend(inputText);
    }
  };

  const insertSymbol = (symbol: string) => {
    setInputText(prev => prev + symbol);
  };

  const deleteChar = () => {
    setInputText(prev => prev.slice(0, -1));
  };

  // Get the last message's suggestions, or default empty
  const lastModelMessage = [...messages].reverse().find(m => m.role === 'model');
  const currentSuggestions = lastModelMessage?.suggestedActions || [];

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col h-full bg-[#f8fafc] relative overflow-hidden font-sans">
        {/* Infinite Grid Background */}
        <div className="absolute inset-0 z-0 opacity-[0.4]" 
             style={{ 
                 backgroundImage: 'radial-gradient(#cbd5e1 1px, transparent 1px)', 
                 backgroundSize: '24px 24px' 
             }}>
        </div>

        {/* Main Workspace Area */}
        <div className={`flex-1 overflow-y-auto z-10 p-4 pb-48 scrollbar-hide transition-all duration-300 ${showKeyboard ? 'pb-[320px]' : ''}`}>
            <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
                {messages.map((msg) => (
                    <div key={msg.id} className={`flex flex-col ${msg.role === 'user' ? 'items-end' : 'items-start'} animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-2 duration-500`}>

                        {/* Avatar Label */}
                        <div className={`flex items-end gap-2 mb-2 px-1 ${msg.role === 'user' ? 'flex-row-reverse' : ''}`}>
                            {msg.role === 'model' && (
                                <div className="mb-[-10px] z-10">
                                    <VoxelChicken size={50} />
                                </div>
                            )}
                            {msg.role === 'user' && (
                                <div className={`w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-sm border-2 bg-indigo-100 border-indigo-200 text-indigo-600`}>
                                    <User size={20} />
                                </div>
                            )}

                            <span className="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">
                                {msg.role === 'user' ? 'You' : 'Prof. Cluck'}
                            </span>
                        </div>

                        {/* Message Card */}
                        <div className={`max-w-[90%] md:max-w-[75%] p-5 rounded-3xl shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed border-b-4 relative
                            ${msg.role === 'user' 
                                ? 'bg-indigo-500 text-white border-indigo-700 rounded-tr-sm' 
                                : 'bg-white border-slate-200 text-slate-700 rounded-tl-sm ml-4'
                            }`}>
                            <p><FormattedText text={msg.text} /></p>
                        </div>

                        {/* Visualization Card */}
                        {msg.visual && msg.visual.type !== VisualType.NONE && (
                            <div className="mt-4 ml-4 w-full max-w-2xl bg-white p-2 rounded-3xl border-2 border-slate-200 shadow-[0_8px_0_rgb(226,232,240)] overflow-hidden">
                                <div className="h-[350px] md:h-[450px] w-full">
                                    {msg.visual.type === VisualType.PLOT && msg.visual.plotData && (
                                        <PlotVis data={msg.visual.plotData} />
                                    )}
                                    {msg.visual.type === VisualType.GRAPH && msg.visual.graphData && (
                                        <GraphVis data={msg.visual.graphData} />
                                    )}
                                    {msg.visual.type === VisualType.MATRIX && msg.visual.matrixData && (
                                        <div className="h-full flex items-center justify-center">
                                            <MatrixVis data={msg.visual.matrixData} />
                                        </div>
                                    )}
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        )}
                    </div>
                ))}

                {isLoading && (
                     <div className="flex flex-col items-start gap-2 animate-pulse">
                         <div className="flex items-end gap-2 px-1">
                             <div className="mb-[-10px] z-10">
                                <VoxelChicken size={50} emotion="thinking" />
                             </div>
                             <span className="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pecking...</span>
                         </div>
                        <div className="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 p-4 rounded-3xl rounded-tl-sm shadow-sm ml-4">
                            <Loader2 className="animate-spin text-brand-green" size={24} />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                )}
                <div ref={messagesEndRef} />
            </div>
        </div>

        {/* Input Area + Keyboard */}
        <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-20 flex flex-col">
            {/* Gradient Fade */}
            <div className="h-12 bg-gradient-to-t from-slate-100 to-transparent pointer-events-none" />

            <div className="bg-slate-100/90 backdrop-blur-md border-t border-slate-200 pb-2 pt-2 px-4">
                <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-3">

                    {/* Suggested Actions Chips */}
                    {!isLoading && !showKeyboard && currentSuggestions.length > 0 && (
                        <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2 justify-center md:justify-start mb-2">
                            {currentSuggestions.map((action, idx) => (
                                <button
                                    key={idx}
                                    onClick={() => handleSend(action)}
                                    className="px-5 py-3 rounded-2xl bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 shadow-[0_4px_0_#e2e8f0] hover:translate-y-1 hover:shadow-none hover:border-brand-blue hover:text-brand-blue font-bold text-slate-600 transition-all text-sm md:text-base flex items-center gap-2 group"
                                >
                                    {action}
                                    <ArrowRight size={16} className="opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity -ml-2 group-hover:ml-0" />
                                </button>
                            ))}
                        </div>
                    )}

                    {/* Input Bar */}
                    <div className="flex items-center gap-3 pb-4">
                         <button 
                            className="p-3 bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-2xl text-slate-400 hover:text-brand-red hover:border-brand-red transition-colors shadow-sm"
                            title="Clear History" 
                            onClick={handleClear}
                        >
                            <Eraser size={20} />
                        </button>

                        <div className="flex-1 relative">
                            <input
                                type="text"
                                value={inputText}
                                onChange={(e) => setInputText(e.target.value)}
                                onKeyDown={handleKeyPress}
                                placeholder="Ask Prof. Cluck..."
                                disabled={isLoading}
                                className={`w-full p-4 pr-12 rounded-2xl border-2 outline-none transition-all font-medium text-slate-700 bg-white border-slate-200 focus:border-brand-blue focus:shadow-[0_4px_0_#1CB0F6]`}
                            />
                            <button 
                                onClick={() => setShowKeyboard(!showKeyboard)}
                                className={`absolute right-2 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 p-2 rounded-xl text-slate-400 hover:bg-slate-100 hover:text-brand-blue transition-colors ${showKeyboard ? 'text-brand-blue bg-blue-50' : ''}`}
                            >
                                {showKeyboard ? <X size={20} /> : <Keyboard size={20} />}
                            </button>
                        </div>

                        <button 
                            onClick={() => handleSend(inputText)}
                            disabled={!inputText.trim() || isLoading}
                            className={`p-4 rounded-2xl transition-all duration-200 flex items-center justify-center
                                ${inputText.trim() && !isLoading 
                                    ? 'bg-brand-green text-white shadow-[0_4px_0_#46A302] hover:translate-y-1 hover:shadow-none' 
                                    : 'bg-slate-200 text-slate-300 cursor-not-allowed'
                                }`}
                        >
                            <Send size={20} />
                        </button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            {/* Custom Math Keyboard */}
            <MathKeyboard 
                isOpen={showKeyboard} 
                onInsert={insertSymbol} 
                onDelete={deleteChar} 
                onEnter={() => handleSend(inputText)} 
            />
        </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Whiteboard;
```

## components/AuthPage.tsx

Replaced the Sparkles icon with the new `VoxelChicken` component for brand consistency.

```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { Sparkles } from 'lucide-react';
import VoxelChicken from './VoxelChicken';

interface AuthPageProps {
  onLogin: () => void;
}

const AuthPage: React.FC<AuthPageProps> = ({ onLogin }) => {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-6 text-center font-sans">
      <div className="mb-8 relative group cursor-pointer" onClick={onLogin}>
        <div className="w-32 h-32 bg-brand-green rounded-3xl rotate-12 absolute -inset-2 opacity-50 blur-lg animate-pulse"></div>
        <div className="w-28 h-28 bg-white border-4 border-slate-100 rounded-3xl flex items-center justify-center relative shadow-xl transform transition-transform group-hover:-translate-y-2 group-hover:rotate-6">
          <VoxelChicken size={80} emotion="happy" />
          <div className="absolute -top-4 -right-4 bg-brand-yellow text-white p-2 rounded-full shadow-lg border-2 border-white animate-bounce">
            <Sparkles size={20} />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h1 className="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-700 mb-4 tracking-tight">
        MathLingo<br/>
        <span className="text-brand-green">Visual Learning</span>
      </h1>

      <p className="text-lg text-slate-500 mb-12 max-w-md font-medium">
        Join <strong>Professor Cluck</strong> and master Calculus, Linear Algebra, and Graph Theory with blocks and fun!
      </p>

      <div className="space-y-4 w-full max-w-sm">
